    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The idea that ignorance of useful employment is an essential characteristic of the true gentleman or lady is contrary to the design of God in the creation of man. Idleness is a sin, and ignorance of common duties is the result of folly, which afterlife will give ample occasion to bitterly regret.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"FE 75.1\" data-link=\"32.303\">Fundamentals of Christian Education, 75</span>.</span></a></sup>",
