    "refcode_short": "AH 92.2",
    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 92.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The ancient custom, though sometimes abused, as by Laban, was productive of good results. When the suitor <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"93\"></span> was required to render service to secure his bride, a hasty marriage was prevented, and there was opportunity to test the depth of his affections, as well as his ability to provide for a family. In our time many evils result from pursuing an opposite course.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">12<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 188.1\" data-link=\"84.777\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 188, 189</span>.</span></a></sup>",
